The paper proposes a neural program generation framework for modeling human question asking, which involves deep learning and natural language processing techniques. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves language modeling and understanding, which suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as another likely sub-category. The paper also involves extensive experiments and evaluation, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves human-computer interaction and cognitive science, which suggests cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as a possible sub-category.
